climbs.name: Tantrum (aka 24)
climbs.fa: (TR) Eric Odenthal, First Lead: Ryan Crochiere, October 2004

content.description:
Start off a 20 foot block leaning against the face and climb a smooth face with vertical seams to a roof then up an offset seam on the featured head-wall above to the top.

Could potentially be lead on just gear.
content.protection: 5 bolts, a couple small cams to 0.5", bolted anchors
content.location:
Left side of the north (downhill) face and just left of

Big Cheese

.

climbs.name: Mouse Trap
climbs.fa: Eric Tipton and Kenn Kenaga, July 2001

content.description:
Climb a chimney past a giant wedged boulder to a ledge then move right to access a short hand crack.

Essentially a lesser quality variation to

Big Cheese

with all of the unpleasant moves in the chimney and none of the good moves higher.
content.location:
Right side of the north (downhill) face and just right of

Tantrum (aka 24)

.

climbs.name: Big Cheese
climbs.fa: Eric Tipton, Kenn Kenaga & Jeff Brennan, July 2001

content.description: Climb a chimney past a giant wedged boulder to a ledge then clip a bolt climb up into a crack leading to the top.
content.location:
Right side of the north (downhill) face and just right of

Tantrum (aka 24)

.
